SIMPLE: perfoliate
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Perfoliate
<hw>Per*fo"li*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>per-</ets> + L. <ets>folium</ets> leaf.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Having the basal part produced around the stem;
-- said of leaves which the stem apparently passes directory
through.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Surrounded by a circle of hairs,
or projections of any kind.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Perforata</ent>⟦br⟧
